As requested on [Twitter|https://twitter.com/AlexPasternak/status/809853578097623040], I'd like a way to disable the built-in Find in Confluence. It is slow to launch and process, and takes up too much space. When just searching for text, I'd much rather just use the built-in browser find.

I typically hit Cmd-F, and start typing, but because it takes so long to come up, you actually type the text you want to search for into the page you're editing. So you have to train yourself to hit Cmd-F, but wait. With the built-in browser find, that is not necessary.

Search and replace is a rare function and I'm fine to launch it another way, or even without a keyboard shortcut. This should not own Cmd-F. Please make this be a user preference at least, thanks.

