*Summary*

Currently, confluence does not have the feature to copy page and copy page tree automatically to different confluence server.

When attempting to delete a page that has child pages, you cannot select the "Also Delete Pages", as the checkbox is disabled. The (!) icon is present, and the tooltip indicates that Confluence is checking permissions.

Looking at a HAR file, the endpoint {{rest/page-hierarchy/internal/subtreeCount/}} is returning {{org.hibernate.exception.GenericJDBCException: could not extract ResultSet}}, due to the following message:
{code:java}
Column 'CONTENT.SPACEID' is invalid in the select list because it is not contained in either an aggregate function or the GROUP BY clause.
{code}
The query being run is defined like this in {{ContentEntityObject.hbm.xml}}:
{code:java}
    <query name="confluence.content_findContentPermissionSummaryByIds"><![CDATA[
        select new com.atlassian.confluence.core.ContentPermissionSummary(content.id, content.space, content.creator) from SpaceContentEntityObject content
        where content.originalVersion is null and
            content.id in (:ids) and
            content.contentStatus = 'current'
        group by content.creator, content.id
    ]]></query>
{code}
Converting this to a usable query gives us:
{code:java}
select CONTENTID, SPACEID, CREATOR
from CONTENT
where PREVVER is null and
CONTENTID in (65545) and
CONTENT_STATUS = 'current'
group by CREATOR, CONTENTID
{code}
The content id was chosen from a local instance, but is relevant. The query (when run manually) gives us:
{code:java}
 [Code: 8120, SQL State: S1000]  Column 'CONTENT.SPACEID' is invalid in the select list because it is not contained in either an aggregate function or the GROUP BY clause.
{code}
Changing the query's {{GROUP BY}} clause to include SPACEID (or content.space in the case of the {{HBM}} file _should_ resolve the issue.

